Uses of Interface
org.cloudbus.cloudsim.utilizationmodels.UtilizationModel

  • Packages that use UtilizationModel 
    Package Description
    org.cloudbus.cloudsim.cloudlets
    The package provides Cloudlet implementations.
    org.cloudbus.cloudsim.cloudlets.network  
    org.cloudbus.cloudsim.utilizationmodels
    The package provides classes that models utilization of resources such as CPU, Ram and Bandwidth, defining how a given resource is used by a Cloudlet along the simulation time.
    org.cloudsimplus.builders
    The package provides Builder classes that implement the Builder Design Pattern to allow instantianting multiple simulation objects more easily.

    • Uses of UtilizationModel in org.cloudbus.cloudsim.utilizationmodels

      Classes in org.cloudbus.cloudsim.utilizationmodels that implement UtilizationModel 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  UtilizationModelArithmeticProgression
      An Cloudlet UtilizationModel that uses Arithmetic Progression to increases the utilization of the related resource along the simulation time.
      class  UtilizationModelFull
      The UtilizationModelFull class is a simple model, according to which a Cloudlet always utilizes a given allocated resource at 100%, all the time.
      class  UtilizationModelPlanetLabInMemory
      Defines the resource utilization model based on a PlanetLab switches trace file.
      class  UtilizationModelStochastic
      Implements a model, according to which a Cloudlet generates random resource utilization every time frame.
      class  UtilizationModelZero
      The UtilizationModelZero class is a simple model, according to which a Cloudlet always require zero capacity for a given resource all the time.
      Fields in org.cloudbus.cloudsim.utilizationmodels declared as UtilizationModel 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static UtilizationModel UtilizationModel.NULL
      A property that implements the Null Object Design Pattern for UtilizationModel objects.
